        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 2:58AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 258 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms in
San Saba County, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Regency, Locker, Cherokee, Chappel, Sloan, Elm Grove, San Saba,
Harkeyville, Richland Springs, Skeeterville, Algerita, Spring Creek,
Hall, Us-190 Near The Mcculloch-
San Saba County Line, and Colorado Bend State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for west central
Texas.</instruction>
